ApmlAuthor(String, Decimal)

Initializes a new instance of the ApmlAuthor class using the supplied parameters.

Declaration
public ApmlAuthor(string key, decimal value)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.String key

The unique key for this author.
System.Decimal value

The decimal score of this author.
Remarks

This constructor is meant to be used when creating an explicit author. Explicit data is for items that are explicitly added by a user to represent something. For example, a user could edit their own APML file and add items they know they're interested in. For this reason the From and UpdatedOn properties are not necessary for explicit data items, because it's a manual process.

Exceptions
Type Condition
System.ArgumentNullException

The key is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).
System.ArgumentNullException

The key is an empty string.
System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException

The value is less than -1.
System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException

The value is greater than 1.

ApmlAuthor(String, Decimal, String, DateTime)

Initializes a new instance of the ApmlAuthor class using the supplied parameters.

Declaration
public ApmlAuthor(string key, decimal value, string from, DateTime utcUpdatedOn)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.String key

The unique key for this author.
System.Decimal value

The decimal score of this author.
System.String from

The name of the entity that contributed this author.
System.DateTime utcUpdatedOn

A System.DateTime object that indicates the last time this author was updated.
Remarks

This constructor is meant to be used when creating an implicit author. Implicit data is added by machines/computers that try to make some informed guesses about the things that you are interested in. This stuff will change over time and are added with a certain degree of confidence that may have a decay in certain applications. For this reason it is important to keep a track of when things were added/modified.

FindExtension(Predicate<ISyndicationExtension>)

Searches for a syndication extension that matches the conditions defined by the specified predicate, and returns the first occurrence within the Extensions collection.

Declaration
public ISyndicationExtension FindExtension(Predicate<ISyndicationExtension> match)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.Predicate<ISyndicationExtension> match

The System.Predicate<T> delegate that defines the conditions of the ISyndicationExtension to search for.
Returns
Type Description
ISyndicationExtension

The first syndication extension that matches the conditions defined by the specified predicate, if found; otherwise, the default value for ISyndicationExtension.
Remarks

The System.Predicate<T> is a delegate to a method that returns true if the object passed to it matches the conditions defined in the delegate. The elements of the current Extensions are individually passed to the System.Predicate<T> delegate, moving forward in the Extensions, starting with the first element and ending with the last element. Processing is stopped when a match is found.

Exceptions
Type Condition
System.ArgumentNullException

The match is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).
